<L>__{interior pacific telephone company switchboard room day}
<A>__{located on grand avenue downtown, the huge switchboard room is a maze of switching stations, tangles of wires and heavy wooden headsets...a roar of buzzers, bells, circuits opening and closing, and a hundred female operators speaking at once. supervisors on skates roll up and down the narrow lanes created by the banks of switching stations, going from one operator to another as needed. christine is one of them. she turns at the sound of a bell struck twice, then rolls down the lane toward an operator frantically waving a pink sheet of paper.}
